In Alpine skiing, Austrian Marcel Hirscher and Slovenian Tina Maze win the overall men's and women's 2013 Alpine Skiing World Cup titles, respectively. (AP via Yahoo! News)UEFA backs Turkish referee Cüneyt Çakır over his controversial decision to red card Manchester United's Nani in last night's elimination by a 2–1 scoreline (3–2 on aggregate) at the feet of Real Madrid in the second leg of their 2012–13 UEFA Champions League last 16 tie at Old Trafford. (The Guardian) (The Independent)